			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2008</a> paper:</span><br><i>A Model Engineering Approach to Tool Interoperability</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/YuSun.html">Yu Sun</a>, <a href="../profile/ZekaiDemirezen.html">Zekai Demirezen</a>, <a href="../profile/FrédéricJouault.html">Frédéric Jouault</a>, <a href="../profile/RobertTairas.html">Robert Tairas</a>, <a href="../profile/JeffreyGGray.html">Jeffrey G. Gray</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_12">10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_12</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagM">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It approaches tool interoperability via model-based mappings/transformations between heterogeneous tool representations.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The method is grounded in a model-engineering tooling stack for enabling interoperability.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6d.html"><span class="tagL">T6D: Synergies</span></a><ul><li> It explicitly bridges tools/communities by applying model engineering techniques to interoperate across ecosystems.
</li></ul></li></ul>
